      "content": "that makes sense, but when u look at the actual datasets, some people argue that it's not just about policing or history. like, if certain groups have higher rates of specific types of crime, doesn't that suggest there might be deeper cultural or even biological factors at play that drive those statistics, rather than just systemic issues? can u address those arguments?",
